metadata.name: Mooving Squigly #171
metadata.description:
A mooving squigly generator inspirated by "Chromie Squiggle by snowfro"
@ArtOnBlockchain on twitter
Made using p5.js

This project aim to be your unique mooving web3 signature

The features define the visual of your squigly
DIFFERENT FEATURES :

    Background Color: #7AA5A6, #FBB900, #FCBF49, #FFFFFF, #F5F3EC, #1F1F1F, #F9EBDC, #F0C328, #8AC1CC
    Squigly Color Theme: flash, chromatic, cloud, kaki, darkred
    Stroke: none, max 10
    Squigly Number: 1, 2, 3
    Special Color Mode: true, false
    Squigly Size: medium, small, large, extra large
    Speed: max 5
    Style: classic, expansion, distortion, blur, gray

The colours and positions are calculated using deterministic perlin noise
Press S to save the squigly
Reload the page to see your squigly moove again

Made with <3 by 0xtedy.tez / @0xtedy
All the code is opensource !
MIT License

metadata.name: string_pllu #4
metadata.description:
Making some abstract plants, inspired by a painting technique called string pull.

Connect some random semi circles with strings and pull the strings from the bottom of the canvas.

The semi circles rotate while moving to create some random brush strokes.

metadata.name: Tesseract #229
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.description:

[z] save alternate artwork as PNG.


Artist note:

Primary royalties are split 95-5% between artist and The Processing Foundation.

Secondary royalties go to the minters (99.9% of the 15%).

metadata.name: Efflorescence #121
metadata.description:
Efflorescence is a piece that bridges between Pouya and Fatima's hand crafted tiles and Gorilla Sun's generative work, and reflects their collective love for patterns and colour. Efflorescence is a generative token that creates unique compositions by random arrangement of different tiles and the colorisation thereof.

This generative token would not have been possible without Zeno Zeng's SVG runtime for P5JS!

Press the down arrow button to export an SVG of the artwork. In live view stroke width can be adjusted by zooming in and out.

metadata.name: PORTOFINO #88
metadata.description:
Portofino is a generative and animated piece creating shapes based on trails.  The size, position and motion frequency of each lines are generated for each token, along with the color theme. Some rare items are available.

Each reloading creates a different movement, as the algorithm underlying the piece is partially based on a noise.

At the end, the animation stop and the visual is created.

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Portofino (Italia).

metadata.name: Sedimentary Dissolution #419
metadata.description:
This piece is inspired by the geological processes related to sedimentary dissolution. Dissolution is a form of weathering which contributes to the creation of new rocks. In this piece, various algorithms take on the role of dissolution, producing visual recombinations of the original "sedimentary rock".

Instructions ::

p : save a hi-res image
e : toggle erosion on and off
s : toggle structure on and off
a : toggle all effects on and off

If offset, rgb dissolution or cross-bedding is true you can toggle it on and off.
If these features are false pressing the key will have no effect.

o : toggle offset on and off
r : toggle rgb dissolution on and off
c : toggle cross-bedding on and off

There are 20 versions you can explore, all using the same features.
Use the left and right arrow to change the random seed. 
Pressing space will re-instantiate the original random seed.

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #995
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Snow Night Generative #77
metadata.description:
Snow night is a particulate artwork for me.
It mix two discipline, 3D art and Generative art, I wanted to give a try with something that I don't really see a lot on FXHash, mixing a 3D world handly created by me and finished by computer, when I say finished by computer is that the computer pick the color (In Six palettes), the snow size and speed for final render of artwork !

I hope you enjoy it !

Made with BabylonJS.

Hash Features :
Six different palettes : 
- Four that have 22.5% chance of being drop
- Monochrome one that have 10% chance of being drop

Radioactivity feature : 5% chances to drop a rare radioactivity features on my artwork !

Two differents snow size : Big and Little
Two differents snow speed : Fast and Slow

Moon Color : Value in RGB

Snow Night by @Disjonquille
Inspired by Jukimoot !

metadata.name: play/plaque #224
metadata.description:
A grid of trailing shapes. Each shape in the line wants to be like the shape in front of it.

The traits
4 shapes: square, cross, triangle, circle
5 grid sizes 1->5 with 1x1 grids being rarest (5%)
2 fill styles: hollow (80%, crosses can't be hollow) and filled (20%)
20% chance for all shapes to be the same
6 color palettes:
- Coffee and Blueberry
- Tropicana
- Monochrome
- Spectrum
- Peach and Pear
- Goji and Kelp

Made by Sam Tsao (@sam___tsao)
